e away from winning in mahjong<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>\u30ef\u30f3\u30bf\u30f3<\/td><td>\u96f2\u5451<\/td><td>\u00a0Wonton<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-footnotes\"><li id=\"3cb5cfd1-fb61-42c8-9965-1c68be668e30\">Both \u548c\u8a9e\u30fb\u502d\u8a9e and \u5927\u548c\u8a00\u8449 may alternatively be used to refer to the Japanese language as a whole.   <a href=\"#3cb5cfd1-fb61-42c8-9965-1c68be668e30-link\" aria-label=\"\u811a\u6ce8\u53c2\u71671\u306b\u30b8\u30e3\u30f3\u30d7\">\u21a9\ufe0e<\/a><\/li><li id=\"720e8856-88d9-4f1d-90d8-f54002c249bc\">Comparative linguistics &#8211; the study of the relationships between two or more languages to discover whether they have a common ancestor &#8211; applied to words believed to be of Japanese origin allows us to safely presume whether a word is truly Japonic to an extent. However, words borrowed into the language before the dawn of the common ancestral language of Japanese may not necessarily be distinguishable from non-loanwords, as their origin may have been lost to history.   <a href=\"#720e8856-88d9-4f1d-90d8-f54002c249bc-link\" aria-label=\"\u811a\u6ce8\u53c2\u71672\u306b\u30b8\u30e3\u30f3\u30d7\">\u21a9\ufe0e<\/a><\/li><li id=\"f2fc74ea-682a-477a-9017-416e8b907d7b\">An example of this is \u8594\u8587\uff08\u3070\u3089\uff09: \/muba\u027ea\/ > \/uba\u027ea\/ > \/iba\u027ea\/ > \/ba\u027ea\/.  <a href=\"#f2fc74ea-682a-477a-9017-416e8b907d7b-link\" aria-label=\"\u811a\u6ce8\u53c2\u71673\u306b\u30b8\u30e3\u30f3\u30d7\">\u21a9\ufe0e<\/a><\/li><li id=\"ae96a396-8d3c-47ff-a835-c0676351225a\">Not all words written with ON readings are of Sino-Japanese origin. Whenever any reading of Kanji, ON or KUN, is used for only its phonetic value, that spelling is known as <em>ateji<\/em>, and one must seek other avenues to determine the word&#8217;s origin.  <a href=\"#ae96a396-8d3c-47ff-a835-c0676351225a-link\" aria-label=\"\u811a\u6ce8\u53c2\u71674\u306b\u30b8\u30e3\u30f3\u30d7\">\u21a9\ufe0e<\/a><\/li><l